## Genre Mapping

**Genre mapping is deferred until after dry-run.** The `--dry-run` mode prints a complete inventory of all unique shelf tags found in the CSV with their counts. Review this output and specify genre mappings before the full import runs.

Design:
- Genre tag ‚Üí CollectCore genre mapping defined in a dict at the top of the script (easy to update between dry-run and full run)
- Genre tags are NOT added as freeform tags ‚Äî they go to `xref_book_item_genres` only
- Multiple genre tags per book = multiple rows in `xref_book_item_genres`
- Any shelf tag not in the genre map, not a library-* tag, and not a known status tag ‚Üí freeform tag
- Genre IDs loaded dynamically from DB at script start

---

## Duplicate Handling

Before inserting: case-insensitive match on title + first author name in `tbl_book_details` + `xref_book_item_authors`. If match found ‚Üí skip, log to `skipped.csv`.

Re-running the script on the same CSV produces 0 new imports (idempotent).

